docs/guides/05-handling-errors.md
     1→# Handling Errors
     3→By default Superstruct throws errors that are easy to understand for developers. This means that out of the box you'll get nice errors messages that help you track down why a piece of data is invalid.
     4→
     5→For example, consider a simple `User` struct:
     6→
     7→```ts
     8→const User = object({
     9→  id: number(),
    10→  name: string(),
    11→  email: email(),
    12→})
    13→```
    14→
    15→If you pass in an invalid email, an error will be thrown:
    16→
    17→```ts
    18→const data = {
    19→  id: 1,
    20→  name: 'Alex',
    21→  email: false,
    22→}
    23→
    24→assert(data, User)
      →…
