docs/guides/06-using-typescript.md
     1→# Using TypeScript
     3→Superstruct is built with TypeScript, and is designed to integrate seamlessly with its guards and assertions. Which means that if you're using TypeScript too you'll get compile-time typings for your data.
     4→
     5→> 🤖 Warning: You must enable TypeScript's [`strictNullChecks`](https://www.typescriptlang.org/tsconfig#strictNullChecks) option in your `tsconfig.json` for Superstruct to work properly with "optional" types. Note that `strictNullChecks` is disabled by default. If you enable `strict`, `strictNullChecks` will automatically be enabled.
     6→
