docs/reference/typescript.md
     1→# TypeScript …
     5→## Utilities …
     7→### `Describe`
     9→The `Describe` utility returns a type representing a struct for a given valid value type. This allows you to ensure you're writing your struct definitions properly, for example:
    10→
    11→```ts
    12→type User = {
    13→  id: number
    14→  name: string
    15→}
    16→
    17→const User: Describe<User> = object({
    18→  id: string(), // This mistake will fail to pass type checking!
    19→  name: string(),
    20→})
    21→```
    22→
      →…
