docs/resources/faq.md
     1→# FAQ
     3→Some common questions you might have when first learning Superstruct.
     4→
     5→### How can I allow unknown keys with `object` structs?
     7→The [`object`](../reference/types.md#object) struct validates that a value matches a known object shape. Just like it's TypeScript counterpart, it does not allow unknown keys—this is very useful in catching bugs in the majority of cases.
     8→
      →…
    11→### Why not have a built-in `json` struct?
    13→The problem with a built-in `json` struct is that it needs to recursively iterate through deep objects to guarantee they're valid JSON. What's wrong with that? Nothing, except that it would be a footgun.
    14→
      →…
docs/resources/links.md
     1→# Resources
     3→A few resources that are helpful for building with Superstruct.
     4→
     5→## Libraries
     7→- [`bumpover`](https://github.com/doodlewind/bumpover) helps you transform data asynchronously with simple rules, whose validation API is built with Superstruct.
     8→- [micro-superstruct](https://github.com/brandon93s/micro-superstruct) allows you to easily validate your [Micro](https://github.com/zeit/micro) API request body and query string parameters using Superstruct.
